place_cells_a..._for_feedthrus(25.10)    place_cells_a..._for_feedthrus(25.10)

Name
       place_cells_at_center_for_feedthrus  -  Places all the instances corre-
       sponding to a given partition and its top interface cells at the center
       to facilitate feedthrough insertion in the flow during  the  floorplan-
       ning stage

Syntax
       place_cells_at_center_for_feedthrus

       [-help]

       [-insts <list_of_selected_insts>]

       [-skipTopInsts]

       Places all the instances corresponding to a given partition and its top
       interface  cells  at  the center to facilitate feedthrough insertion in
       the flow during the floorplanning stage.  It quickly changes the design
       status to "placed" by placing all unplaced cells of the  partition  and
       top in the middle of the partition, so that feedthrough can be run.

       Note: The place_cells_at_center_for_feedthrus command places only those
       unplaced  cells of the partition(s) and top that interact with the par-
       tition interface. All other unplaced cells will remain unplaced.

       Note: It places all the cells on the same location (overlapping).

       Note: It can handle rectilinear partition fences and nested designs.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each place_cells_at_center_for_feedthrus parame-
              ter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man place_cells_at_center_for_feedthrus

       -insts <list_of_selected_insts>
              Specifies  the  name of the instances that will be placed at the
              center of the partition.

              You can use wildcards (*?) with this parameter.

              For example, the following command  places  all  unplaced  cells
              that have ECO in their name to the center of the partition:

              place_cells_at_center_for_feedthrus -insts *ECO*

              Data_type: string, optional

       -skipTopInsts
              Skips placing the cells of top instances at the center.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       The  following command changes the design status to "placed" by placing
       all unplaced cells in the middle of the partition, so that  feedthrough
       can be run.

       place_cells_at_center_for_feedthrus

